Hi, Brian --

There is no correct first step.  8*7=56 and 28*2=56, so either first 
step is valid.  The only part of the process that can be correct or 
not is the final prime factorization.  Regardless of which way you 
start out, in the end the only correct prime factorization is 
2*2*2*7.

- Doctor Greenie, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

